22/03/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Dragan Covic will not resign as the BiH presidency's Croat member, despite indictments against him and increasing Western pressure. Leaders of Covic's Croat Democratic Union met in Mostar on Monday (21 March) and issued a statement expressing full support for him and rejecting the charges against him as politically motivated. Covic and six others face charges of embezzlement and abuse of office, stemming from his term as Federation of BiH finance minister. 
In other news Monday, the BiH State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) and the entities' police agencies sealed a memorandum on co-operation and co-ordination in protecting state facilities as well as individuals. SIPA will begin training more than 140 additional police troops as guards. (Dnevni avaz - 22/03/05; Pincom.info, NTV Hayat, RTRS - 21/03/05)
